{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"YAML syntax error causes error message that includes the offending line number","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: The failure is in the error-handling wrapper around the YAML parser: does it extract the line number from the parser's exception and include it in the user-facing message? This is one try/except block's output. REAL-INFRA: The real YAML parser (PyYAML / ruamel.yaml) must be exercised — not mocked — because the test verifies that the exception object emitted by the parser actually carries line-number information that the handler surfaces. However, YAML parsing operates entirely on an in-memory string; no file I/O is required to produce the error. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the parser would hide whether it provides line numbers and whether the handler reads the right attribute. The real parser must run, but it runs on a string, keeping this at Unit. REJECTION-GATE: Integration was considered but the YAML parser is an in-process library call, not a module boundary that requires wiring.","test_description":"Supply a multi-line YAML string that has a deliberate syntax error on a known line N (e.g., line 3). Pass this string to the loader's config-parse function. Assert that the resulting error message or exception string contains the integer N (or a substring like 'line 3').","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.85,"Integration":0.12,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Missing config directory is created and defaults file is written on first run","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: This behavior spans two observable side-effects — directory creation and file writing — that must survive a full loader startup sequence, not just a single function call. The failure could be in the existence check, the mkdir call, or the file-write call failing silently; any of these bugs spans module boundaries (startup orchestrator → filesystem layer → defaults writer). REAL-INFRA: Mocking `os.makedirs` and `open` would confirm call counts but not that the correct directory path was created or that the written defaults file contains valid content. An in-process temp directory lets the real I/O code run and produces artifacts that can be directly inspected — this is the minimal infrastructure that cannot be faked away without hiding real failures. MOCK-HIDE: Mocking the filesystem hides wrong-path bugs and content correctness bugs. LLM-DEP: None. REJECTION-GATE: System was considered but directory creation/file writing does not require a real subprocess, real OS signals, or real external network; a temp-directory integration test is sufficient.","test_description":"Use `tmp_path` (pytest fixture) as the config root. Patch the loader's config-home resolution to return a subdirectory of `tmp_path` that does not yet exist. Run the loader's startup function. Assert that (a) the config directory now exists on disk, and (b) a defaults file exists at the expected path with non-empty, valid YAML content.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.13,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9759,"cache_read_input_tokens":3199,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9759},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5c7c6802-611f-4bf6-81b6-a5eb68e9f6f3","uuid":"8ed5bbf7-ea9b-44c4-b266-57d62a094264"}
